Bug.WithStack:
Using RC2
Steps to recreate: 1. Run > Debug 2. Create a new Java Application LaunchConfig 3. Enter a project name with a \ or / in the name 4. Observe error log
Reason for bug: JavaMainTab uses IWorkspaceRoot.getProject(String) to see whether a project exists. The implementation WorkspaceRoot.getProject(String) asserts that the project name consists of exactly one segment, which is not the case on an empty project name (0) or one with path seperators.
Proposed solution: Use IWorkspaceRoot.findMember(string) instead.
