source_code.code:
if (storedKey.length - bytesToOmit == key.length) {
	HistoryStoreEntry storedEntry = HistoryStoreEntry.create(store, 
cursor);
	if (!visitor.visit(storedEntry))
		break;
        else {
           cursor.next();
           continue;
        }
   }

Bug.WithStack:
In the HistoryStore.accept(...) logic, we first check for an exact match 
between the key passed in and the key stored on disk.  If we find an exact 
match, we call the visitor.  If the visitor returns true, we should move onto 
the next key that matches the key passed in.  There is no need to check for a 
partial match or a match where the last character is a separator, etc.  This 
is wasted processing time.  Instead, the code should look like:

  if (storedKey.length - bytesToOmit == key.length) {
	HistoryStoreEntry storedEntry = HistoryStoreEntry.create(store, 
cursor);
	if (!visitor.visit(storedEntry))
		break;
        else {
           cursor.next();
           continue;
        }
   }
Fixed and released to HEAD.

